{"id": "1441147599376748584", "channel_id": "1441147599376748584", "type": 0, "author_id": "469060950310518795", "author_name": "ourwordsfly_gabriele", "author_bot": false, "content": "I've been having this problem since yesterday's update.\nThe resources download gets stuck as shown in the attached image.\n In this one instance it's been stuck like this for about 1 hour and it's not having any sign of changing as I'm writing this post.\nNow, as I said, this happened yesterday as well, my course of actions so far as been:\n1. Tried to exit the game via alt F4, since a friend of mine got out of a similar situation by doing ,this and reopened the game. It didn't work out. Upon opening the game again it showed to be downloading 0.00 B out of 0.00 B.\n2. Closed the game and verified data files on Steam. The problem persisted.\n3. Used the in-game fix button, re-downloading 700 MB of update. This seemed promising at first but a couple unusual things happened: \n- Even tho the game's data download wasn't done (around 600 MB), the progress bar displayed a 100 percent completion.\n-Upon reaching 700 MB, it started downloading another 50 MB and then got stuck again.\n\nThe only thing I haven't tried to do yet is disinstalling the game and then re install it again. I truly wish to keep it as the very last option tho.\nThis pretty much goes over everything. I await for any kind of feedback. In the meanwhile I'll try to verify the files and using the fix button again to see if anything changes, but I'm not too hopefull.\nThank in advance.", "timestamp": "2025-11-20T19:26:02.919000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [{"id": "1441147599649374248", "filename": "20251120200641_1.jpg", "content_type": "image/jpeg", "size": 164940, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1441147599376748584/1441147599649374248/20251120200641_1.jpg?ex=69ff8a4a&is=69fe38ca&hm=5cb6ab28332cb4df978136272e1248883a8eff75bf1c1e96abe688b4d